\cos(x+\phi_i)
\cos x
\sin x
\begin{align} \sum_{i=1}^N a_i \cos(x+\phi_i) &= \sum_{i=1}^N a_i\left(\cos x \cos\phi_i - \sin x\sin \phi_i \right) \\ &= \cos x \sum_{i=1}^N a_i \cos\phi_i - \sin x \sum_{i=1}^N a_i \sin \phi_i \\ &=: p \cos x - q \sin x \end{align}
x
p
q
r
\theta
(1)
p = r \cos \theta \qquad q = r \sin \theta \qquad \qquad (1)
p \cos x - q \sin x = r \cos x \cos \theta - r \sin x \sin\theta = r \left( \cos x \cos\theta - \sin x \sin\theta \right) = r \cos(x+\theta)
p \cos x - q \sin x = r \cos \left(x + \theta\right)
